people. But, beyond that the spell isnt that spiffy.<br>
<br>
The risk of getting a rather crappy 2.0 effiency (1200), with the odd kinda nice 5.0 effiency if you land a full 3000. But, toss in partial resists and you can see alot of hits for 500dmg and what not which is just pretty much pathetic.<br>
<br>
So, my thought is<br>
<br>
- Why not make the min damage on this spell 2400, this would give the 'min' random range an effiency of 4.0. Slightly less then solro's nuke, but hell, druids get nukes that are like 4.0 effiency or damn near, so why not.<br>
<br>
- up the max damage to 3600, for a 6.0 dmg/mana effiency <br>
<br>
Using minitab (go go stab22f, I hate that class), in a theortical 10,000 castings if no partial resists, the avg dmg would be 2997 or 4.9 effiency<br>
<br>
and my thought is - wizards should be nuking at 5.0 effiency anyways considering how many classes are creeping up on the 4.0 mark with our best being 4.2, + they got more to offer.<br>
<br>
Now and then, we'd get a nice 6.0 dmg/mana effiency (pre crits/aa's/focus/etc) and a nice DPS ..<br>
<br>
dont think that'd be to much to ask for out of a lvl 65 spell, considering how hard they are to obtain. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=elyia>Elyia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 155<br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/18/02 12:41 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Shock of Magic</span><hr size=1> Rather then changing the spell I'd like to see a unique focus item that ups the minimum damage of Shock of Magic.  Be something nice to look forward to.  Making equipment useful is always a good thing. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://home.earthlink.net/~kosmos00/elyiasig.gif"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:xx-small;"><br>
