<!--EZCODE HR START--><hr /><!--EZCODE HR END--><br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Shock of Magic:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
1200 to 3000 Damage<br>
<br>
600 mana/6 sec Cast Time.<br>
<br>
Raw data.<br>
<!--EZCODE HR START--><hr /><!--EZCODE HR END--><br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>How much can this actual hit for?</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Last Crit I saw was around 6709 with this spell. <br>
<br>
Focus items + SCM 3 + Crit Modifier for wizards. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Is this the most you will see, or will it hit 7k?</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>How Much Mana will you actual use with top end gear and w/o full AA modifiers</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->?<br>
<br>
Spell Haste + AA.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Cast time 6.0 secs, whats it down to with Spell Haste and AA's? Under 5.0 secs? No Recast time.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<br>
Don't get me wrong I love seeing High End Crits.. they do make me smile.. the Mob dead is what really matters in the end. I thought this spell was pretty unique when I read up on it.. and it seems to me and maybe this is the intention of the spell, but .. it  only get better as you gain better focus and AA's. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Reason for this pondering:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Caution  - <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>unique focus item that ups the minimum damage of Shock of Magic -Elyia<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
.. requiring a focus item for a particular spell.. that may set a principle and be more of a PITA.. and really the only reason I am commenting.. currently I am having that dilemma as a Druid. <br>
<br>
Looking for Focus items that meets my needs:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>A)</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> increase my Healing potential (overall) ( <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>We are Limited on Haste, Efficiency, etc. due to Percentage Healing and CH being blocked by Focus items</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->)<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>B)</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> increasing spell haste<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>C)</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> increasing damage<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>D)</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> spell mana savings for DoTs (Affliction Efficiency)<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>E)</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> spell DoT Duration (Extended Affliction)<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>F)</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> spell haste for DoTs (Affliction Haste)<br>
<br>
Yea, headache.. can't have it all so I basically have to stand back and wait and see the items that drop and then make a decision later down the road.. but the dilemma comes down to.. progression into the Elemental Planes and not going back to other the lower tiers and possibly missing out on an item I &quot;did&quot; in fact require. - My dilemma.<br>
<br>
Basically what I am saying... is there room for &quot;Focus specific items for particular spells?&quot; Will a trend develop into other classes? I realize only one person here in this short thread has asked for it, but it is something I am really highly against.<br>
<br>
I am not trying to go overboard on this.. I just see it having a dominoe effect and instead of helping.. it would create even more problems .. and possibly open up Pandora's box so to speak.  <br>
<br>
I have apologized ahead of time if I did offend anyone. <p><hr><body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" link="#FFFF00" vlink="#00FF00" alink="#00FF00"><div align="center"><center><table border="3" cellspacing="0" bordercolor="#008080" bordercolordark="#000000" bordercolorlight="#008080"><tr><td valign="top" width="100%" background="http://www.thedruidsgrove.org/images/sobe/back.gif"><p align="center"><font color="#80FF00" size="4" face="Trebuchet MS"><strong>Sobe Silvertree</strong></font><font color="#FFFF80" face="Trebuchet MS"><br></font><font color="#FFFF80" size="2" face="Trebuchet MS">"</font><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=283084" target="_blank"><font color="#FFFF80" size="2" face="Trebuchet MS">The Wanderer</font></a><font color="#FFFF80" size="2" face="Trebuchet MS">" and "</font><a href="http://www.geocities.com/kibadachi_uk/epiclink.htm" target="_blank"><font color="#FFFF80" size="2" face="Trebuchet MS">First Tunarian Protector</a>"</font><font color="#FFFF80" size="2" face="Trebuchet MS"><br>Elder Storm Warden of </font><a href="http://www.afterlifeguild.org/" target="_blank"><font color="#FFFF80" size="2" face="Trebuchet MS">Guild Afterlife</font></a><font color="#FFFF80" size="2" face="Trebuchet MS"><br>Administrator of </font><font color="#FFFF80" size="2" face="Trebuchet MS"></font><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthedruidsgrove" target="_blank"><font color="#FFFF80" size="2" face="Trebuchet MS">The Druids Grove</a><br><font color="#FFFF80" size="2" face="Trebuchet MS">Sobe's </font><a href="http://www.afterlifeguild.org/dkp.cgi?history=Sobe;htype=Kills;sort=last_kill" target="_blank"><font color="#FFFF80" size="2" face="Trebuchet MS">Last Kill</a></font></p></td></tr></table></center></div></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zurrenal>Zurren AL</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 412<br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/18/02 11:21 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: hmm..</span><hr size=1> for some reason, ez boards butchered the post and took out a random sentance here and there.. to lazy to fix it for now...<br>
 <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zurrenal>Zurren AL</A> at: 12/18/02 11:22:23 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=aiyanenfarre>Aiyane N Farre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br>  Posts: 201<br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/18/02 1:08 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Shock of Magic</span><hr size=1> I do think we might suggest they take a look at this spell. In almost all situations Agnar's Thunder is a better spell. There are only a few times you'd use SoM.<br>
<br>
Agnar's does 2305dmg for 580mana in 7 sec with resist mod 0.<br>
Shock of Magic is 1200 - 3000dmg for 600mana in 6sec with resist mod +20.<br>
<br>
Average damage on SoM should be 2100 giving an efficiency of 3.5 compared to 2305dmg at 3.97 eff. for Agnar's. SoM also has the +20 resist modifier making it easier to resist. SoM's faster cast time gives it, theoreticly, a slightly better DPS but with higher resists will you get actual better DPS? Doubtfull. If you are fighting a mob that needs to die as fast as possible SoM might look like a good idea but its mobs like that that are more likely to have higher resists so SoM will actually turn out worse.<br>
<br>
If they upped the min damage to 1500 it would raise the avg to 2250 and eff. to 3.75. The increased avg. damage might be enough to overcome the extra resists and give actual higher DPS.<br>
<br>
edit: fixed avg dmg <p>Aiyane N'Farre<br>
