</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=aiyanenfarre>Aiyane N Farre</A> at: 12/19/02 7:40:32 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=midgetgod>Midget God</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br>  Posts: 202<br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/18/02 2:48 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Shock of Magic</span><hr size=1> I like the idea of making focus items to increase the minimum dmg of spells. But instead of making it spell specific have one for fire, cold, and magic nukes and hell, maybe a very rare one for all elements. <p>[60 Sorcerer] <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=69194">Zuratuli</a> (Gnome) <<a href="http://www.insublimity.com">Sublimity</a>></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zurrenal>Zurren AL</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 414<br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/18/02 3:10 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Shock of Magic</span><hr size=1> In short ...<br>
<br>
-- Personnaly, I dont think that spells should be balanced with AA's in mind, but AA's should be tuned with spells in mind, and if anything, should be considered butter ontop of what is allready there. Perhaps a nieve way to want to look at it, but why should a wiz need to spend AA and find focus items to compete with nukes that other class's get when they are supposed to be the best? dmg is all they bring to the table in a group really (sure, snare here and there, and evac.. druids get that to, ooo)<br>
<br>
-- SoM, in theory should have an avg dmg/mana ratio of 3.5. However, due to the +20 resist check, partial resists are more common, lowering that number greatly. If it was on a lure, or near lure check that 3.5 ideal number would be a bit more hopefull.<br>
<br>
-- Wizards really need a 'great nuke' to set them apart, and I think SoM should/could be the one to do it, if they were to lower the resist on the spell so its less resistant then draught (but more resistant then lures), and make the minimum dmg effiency at 4.0, with the max being 6.0 .. it would really give wizards that little bit of 'unf'. and I'm sure SoE could tune the spell to make it hit the 4.0 range more often then spiking upto 6.0, but it would still make for a nice extra kick now and then.<br>
<br>
-- I dislike of having focus items for specific spells, its allready annoying enough having focus items for specific resists (fire, cold, magic, etc), I would rather it just be kept to the genrealized mana conv I, II, III, IV, etc. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=enoah35>Enoah35</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 525<br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/19/02 4:14 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Shock of Magic</span><hr size=1> Make it as spell like they did to Iceflame of E'ci. It affects only lvl 60 ice line spells ( make that a fixed 30% increase damit !1!1!!). Hows that?<br>
<br>
Enoah <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=znailvh>Znail vh</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 524<br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/19/02 6:37 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Shock of Magic</span><hr size=1> The only thing that anoys me is the resist mod. Removing it or even reversing it would do the trick in making this spell good. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zurrenal>Zurren AL</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 419<br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/21/02 3:32 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Shock of Magic</span><hr size=1> Yeah, the +resist mod makes the spell far to unreliable, was playing with it the other night and kept seeing it land for damage in the 100s range .. getting the rare crit for like, 6.9k is nice, but does not offset the unreliability of the spell.<br>
<br>
Turn the resist mod to ooh, -100 .. and then it may be far more usefull. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=qaman>Qaman</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 1960<br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/23/02 11:55 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Shock of Magic</span><hr size=1> To make it more useful, get rid of the resist mod. For the level of the spell, it makes no real sense. If nothing else, make it 0. And make the minimum damage more along the lines of 1600-1800. That would make the avg spell damage 2300-2400, which would be more along the lines that would be expected for spells at this level. The fact that it can do 3000 damage is already balanced by the fact you can do minimum damage. VI tends to go way to far when adding on the detrimental parts of balance, such that they end up rendering the entire spell mostly useless as was the case with Disintegrate. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4380">Qaman</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
Arcanist - <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.eternalwrath.org"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;">Eternal Wrath</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
Ayonae Ro</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mysthyl>Mysthyl</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 484<br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/27/02 3:58 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> som</span><hr size=1> Shock of magic is a horrid spell plain and simple. Its average efficiency is lower then agnarr's when you add that to its high resist rate and the unreliable nature of the spell (hitting for 1200 when you really NEED a 2k+ nuke) you are left with a very sorry spell indeed.<br>
<br>
Got 2 ideas to fix it. <br>
<br>
